# RAG & Retrieval Rules

## Retrieval is called exactly once per violation
- act_retrieval.py is called once in act_pipeline.py — never call it inside evaluators
- Results are stored in ViolationContext and reused by all downstream steps

## Hybrid scoring formula (do not change weights without updating config.py)
final_score = 0.5 × cosine + 0.3 × BM25 + 0.2 × law_boost

## Empty collection handling
- If all 3 collections are empty → return ViolationContext with empty lists, score=0.0
- Never raise exception on empty retrieval — log warning instead
- Downstream steps must check: if not context.retrieved_norms → handle gracefully

## Indexing rules
- Always index to all 3 collections: norms, typical_violations, historical_checklists
- Minimum document metadata fields: source, date, law_ref, collection_name
- Re-indexing must be idempotent — use document ID as ChromaDB ID to avoid duplicates

## What NOT to do
- Do not embed text longer than 512 tokens — chunk first
- Do not store raw PDF bytes in ChromaDB — store extracted text only
- Do not bypass BM25 cache — always use bm25_cache.py interface